<i>♪ Flies...</i>

19:05.400 --> 19:07.767
"There would be headlines in the papers."

19:07.840 --> 19:10.844
"Even the guys who ran the betting at the wrestling

19:10.960 --> 19:13.247
and the barrow boys would hear with respect

19:13.320 --> 19:15.971
how Old Misery's house had been destroyed."

19:16.880 --> 19:20.521
"It was as though this plan
had been with him all his life,

19:20.600 --> 19:22.682
pondered through the seasons,

19:22.800 --> 19:27.408
now in his 15th year crystallised
with the pain of puberty."

19:30.200 --> 19:34.683
What is Graham Greene trying
to communicate with this passage?

19:34.800 --> 19:38.009
Why did the children break into Old Misery's house?

19:38.800 --> 19:41.883
- Joanie?
- They wanted to rob him.

19:41.960 --> 19:44.964
Joanie, if you had actually read the story,

19:45.040 --> 19:47.964
which at 13 pages would have taken you all night,

19:48.080 --> 19:52.642
you would know the children find a
great deal of money in the mattress.

19:52.720 --> 19:55.121
But they burn it.

19:57.480 --> 19:59.801
Donnie Darko,

19:59.880 --> 20:02.724
perhaps with your recent brush with mass destruction

20:02.840 --> 20:05.081
you can give us your opinion.

20:05.200 --> 20:09.569
Well, they say when they flood
the house and tear it to shreds

20:09.640 --> 20:12.371
that destruction is a form of creation,

20:12.480 --> 20:15.609
so the fact that they burn the money is ironic.

20:16.200 --> 20:20.091
They just want to see what happens
when they tear the world apart.

20:20.160 --> 20:22.049
They wanna change things.

20:22.400 --> 20:24.607
[Door opens]

20:28.680 --> 20:30.170
May we help you?

20:31.000 --> 20:34.368
I just registered. They put me
in the wrong English class.

20:34.440 --> 20:36.966
You look like you belong here.

20:37.880 --> 20:40.451
Um, where do I sit?

20:43.720 --> 20:46.644
Next to the boy you think is the cutest.

20:46.760 --> 20:51.607
- [Excited voices]
- Quiet. Let her choose.

21:11.600 --> 21:13.489
Joanie, get up.

21:36.760 --> 21:40.446
The construction guys
say it'll take a week to fix the roof.

21:40.520 --> 21:43.444
That airline better not fuck us
on the shingle match.

21:44.800 --> 21:47.690
- They still don't know?
- Know what?

21:47.800 --> 21:49.928
Where it came from.

21:50.000 --> 21:53.209
No. Apparently they can't tell us what happened yet.

21:53.280 --> 21:58.207
Something about a matching
serial number that got burned.

21:58.280 --> 22:03.650
I had to sign a form saying
I wouldn't talk to anyone about it.

22:03.720 --> 22:07.008
We're not supposed to tell anyone
what nobody knows?

22:07.080 --> 22:09.003
Yeah.

22:09.080 --> 22:13.404
But you tell...
What's your doctor's name?

22:13.480 --> 22:15.926
- Dr. Thurman, Dad.
- Yes.

22:16.000 --> 22:18.844
You tell Dr. Thurman whatever you want.

22:19.240 --> 22:20.924
- Dad.
- What?

22:21.000 --> 22:22.729
Dad!

22:24.560 --> 22:26.608
[Dog barking]

22:45.360 --> 22:47.886
No mail today. Maybe tomorrow.

22:51.760 --> 22:55.082
[Whispers]

23:04.720 --> 23:07.007
Well, what did she say to you?

23:13.920 --> 23:17.606
- I made a new friend.
- Real or imaginary?

23:17.680 --> 23:19.489
Imaginary...

23:19.560 --> 23:21.403
Would you like to talk about him?

23:21.520 --> 23:24.729
- Frank.
- Frank.

23:24.840 --> 23:28.083
- What did Frank say?
- To follow him.

23:28.160 --> 23:30.288
- Where?
- Into the future.

23:31.600 --> 23:33.921
And then what happens?

23:35.280 --> 23:37.806
And then he said...

23:38.400 --> 23:42.086
Then he said the world was coming to an end.

23:42.160 --> 23:44.481
Do you think it is?

23:49.880 --> 23:51.962
No.

23:53.600 --> 23:55.489
That's stupid.

23:57.160 --> 24:01.165
<i>[TV] For my entire life I was a victim of fear.</i>

24:02.640 --> 24:04.449
<i>Love.</i>

24:05.480 --> 24:08.609
<i>I was feeding fear through food.</i>

24:13.040 --> 24:14.883
<i>Fear.</i>

24:21.320 --> 24:23.721
<i>Finally I looked in the mirror.</i>

24:23.800 --> 24:28.408
<i>Not just in the mirror. I looked through the mirror.</i>

24:28.480 --> 24:32.804
<i>In that image I saw my ego reflection.</i>

24:35.520 --> 24:39.286
<i>I thought ten-year-olds normally wet the bed.</i>

24:40.160 --> 24:42.242
- [Snorts]
- Shh!

24:46.200 --> 24:49.249
<i>The solution was there all the time.</i>

24:50.000 --> 24:52.082
<i>I'm not afraid any more!</i>

24:53.080 --> 24:58.211
<i>All over America, people have
come together to join hands.</i>

24:59.000 --> 25:05.963
<i>People who believe that human life
is absolutely too important,</i>

25:06.040 --> 25:11.410
<i>too valuable and too precious
to be controlled by fear.</i>

25:14.720 --> 25:16.324
<i>Hello.</i>

25:16.400 --> 25:20.007
<i>My name is Jim Cunningham.
Welcome to Controlling Fear.</i>

25:32.000 --> 25:34.480
<i>[Frank] Wake up, Donnie.</i>

26:11.960 --> 26:16.602
"And the prince was led into a world
of strange and beautiful magic."

26:16.720 --> 26:18.529
Hey, guess what!

26:18.600 --> 26:20.807
I can't believe it!

26:21.920 --> 26:24.446
The school is closed today because it's flooded.

26:24.560 --> 26:26.722
- No way.
- Yes.

26:26.800 --> 26:29.804
Holy shit! That's the best news I've ever heard.

26:36.440 --> 26:39.444
My God. Is this ever gonna stop?

26:39.520 --> 26:44.367
Eventually, yes. But I've got
12 classrooms full of water,

26:44.480 --> 26:47.324
all coming from a busted water main.

26:47.400 --> 26:50.529
- What else?
- What else?!

26:50.600 --> 26:53.331
Principal Cole, I'll show you what else.

26:56.440 --> 26:59.887
- Unbelievable.
- That's solid bronze, isn't it?

27:00.000 --> 27:01.809
How did this happen?

27:02.480 --> 27:06.769
The boys' locker room was flooded.
They found faeces everywhere.

27:06.840 --> 27:09.764
- What are faeces?
- Baby mice.

27:28.440 --> 27:30.522
<i>Hey.</i>

27:30.600 --> 27:33.888
Has anyone ever told you that you're sexy?

27:34.000 --> 27:36.924
- I like your boobs.
- [Boys laugh]

27:37.000 --> 27:38.525
<i>Hey.</i>

27:39.360 --> 27:41.727
<i>Hey.</i>

27:41.800 --> 27:43.962
School's cancelled.

27:46.160 --> 27:48.322
Do you want to walk me home?

27:49.040 --> 27:51.168
Sure.

27:59.480 --> 28:02.086
- Don't look so freaked.
- I'm not.

28:02.200 --> 28:05.886
Check your backpack.
Those guys love to steal shit.

28:09.840 --> 28:13.367
- Why did you move here?
- My parents got a divorce.

28:13.440 --> 28:16.762
My mom got a restraining order against my stepdad.

28:16.880 --> 28:21.920
- He has emotional problems.
- Me too. What kind does he have?

28:22.040 --> 28:25.283
He stabbed my mom four times in the chest.

28:26.240 --> 28:29.130
Oh. Did he go to jail?

28:29.880 --> 28:32.929
No, he fled. They still can't find him.

28:33.000 --> 28:38.530
Mom and I had to change our names.
I thought Gretchen Ross was cool.

28:38.600 --> 28:40.841
I was in jail once.

28:40.920 --> 28:43.730
I accidentally burned down this house.

28:43.840 --> 28:45.922
It was abandoned, but still...

28:46.000 --> 28:50.369
I got held back in school,
I can't drive till I'm 21.

28:50.440 --> 28:53.046
But I'm over all of that. I...

28:53.120 --> 28:56.806
I'm painting and stuff. Writing.

28:56.920 --> 29:00.845
I want to be a writer. Maybe a painter.
Maybe both.

29:00.920 --> 29:04.242
I'll write a book and draw the pictures.

29:04.400 --> 29:07.882
Then maybe people will
understand me. Change things.

29:07.960 --> 29:09.849
Donnie Darko?

29:09.920 --> 29:14.687
What the hell kind of name is that?
It's like some sort of superhero.

29:14.760 --> 29:16.888
What makes you think I'm not?

29:21.560 --> 29:23.449
Look, I should go.

29:23.520 --> 29:26.285
Monnitoff wants me to write this physics essay.

29:26.360 --> 29:29.489
Greatest invention ever to benefit mankind.

29:30.880 --> 29:35.761
If it's Monnitoff, that's easy. Antiseptics.

29:35.880 --> 29:40.204
The whole sanitation thing.
Joseph Lister, 1895.

29:40.280 --> 29:42.487
Before antiseptics there was no sanitation.

29:42.560 --> 29:46.246
