that he perceives to be threatening.

55:21.920 --> 55:24.491
Has he ever told you about his friend Frank?

55:29.240 --> 55:31.527
Frank?

55:31.640 --> 55:33.483
The giant bunny rabbit.

55:34.320 --> 55:36.209
What?

55:40.160 --> 55:45.849
I don't recall him ever having mentioned a rabbit.

55:45.920 --> 55:50.926
Donnie is experiencing what is called
a daylight hallucination.

55:54.680 --> 55:58.480
This is a common occurrence
among paranoid schizophrenics.

56:00.560 --> 56:02.642
What can we do?

56:02.720 --> 56:06.930
I would like to do more hypnotherapy.

56:09.080 --> 56:11.401
And increase his medication.

56:15.760 --> 56:17.922
[Thunderclap]

56:18.040 --> 56:23.604
Whatever will help him, really,
because that's why we're here.

56:23.680 --> 56:28.766
We just would like him to experience some... relief.

56:28.840 --> 56:33.687
So if you think that more medication will do that,

56:33.760 --> 56:38.129
then I think we should give it a try.

56:38.880 --> 56:41.531
[Bells chime]

56:50.880 --> 56:52.928
Donnie Darko.

56:55.800 --> 56:57.848
I know.

56:57.920 --> 57:00.651
[Both laugh]

57:01.840 --> 57:03.763
[music and applause]

57:07.040 --> 57:09.930
- Good morning, you Mongrels.
- Good morning.

57:10.000 --> 57:13.083
Is that all the gusto you can muster?
Good morning!

57:13.200 --> 57:15.328
Good morning.

57:15.400 --> 57:17.721
Now, that's a tiny bit better.

57:17.800 --> 57:23.204
But I can sense some students
who are afraid to say good morning.

57:23.280 --> 57:25.408
[Students] Good morning!

57:25.480 --> 57:27.448
That's what I like to hear!

57:27.560 --> 57:30.530
Entirely too many
young men and women today

57:30.600 --> 57:33.649
are completely paralysed by their fears.

57:33.800 --> 57:38.601
They surrender their bodies
to the temptation and destruction

57:38.720 --> 57:41.769
of drugs, alcohol and premarital sex.

57:42.680 --> 57:46.730
Now, I'm gonna tell you a little story today.

57:46.840 --> 57:48.968
It's a heartbreakingly sad story

57:49.040 --> 57:53.329
about a young man
whose life was completely destroyed

57:53.400 --> 57:55.607
by these instruments of fear.

57:55.720 --> 58:01.090
A young man searching for love
in all the wrong places.

58:01.840 --> 58:04.207
His name was Frank.

58:08.920 --> 58:13.369
Um, my stepsister...
I sometimes worry that she eats too much.

58:13.440 --> 58:16.091
- Shut up, Kim.
- Sweetheart, please.

58:16.160 --> 58:20.643
- What can I do when I grow up?
- That's a hard one.

58:20.720 --> 58:22.802
How do I learn how to fight?

58:22.880 --> 58:25.884
"How do I learn how to fight?"

58:25.960 --> 58:30.284
Son, violence is a product of fear.

58:30.400 --> 58:33.529
- Learn to truly love yourself.
- OK.

58:33.600 --> 58:35.967
- Get up here.
- OK.

58:36.040 --> 58:38.202
All right.

58:40.320 --> 58:43.403
- Good morning.
- [Jim] Good morning.

58:43.520 --> 58:46.490
Um, how much are they paying you
to be here?

58:48.000 --> 58:49.525
Excuse me?

58:51.720 --> 58:53.324
What is your name, son?

58:53.400 --> 58:55.289
Gerald.

58:55.360 --> 58:58.443
Gerald, I think you're afraid.

58:58.520 --> 59:03.970
Are you telling us this so we buy your
book? It's the worst advice I heard.

59:04.040 --> 59:05.929
You see how sad this is?

59:06.000 --> 59:11.769
Want your sister to lose weight? Tell
her to get off the couch and exercise.

59:11.880 --> 59:15.009
No-one knows what to do when they grow up.

59:15.080 --> 59:18.766
It takes a while to find that out. Right, Jim?

59:18.840 --> 59:20.888
And you.

59:20.960 --> 59:22.962
Yeah, you.

59:23.080 --> 59:26.129
You sick of some jerk picking on you?

59:26.200 --> 59:29.602
Maybe you should lift weights or do karate.

59:29.720 --> 59:32.485
Next time he tries, kick him in the balls.

59:32.560 --> 59:33.641
[Gasps]

59:33.720 --> 59:35.529
[Jim laughs] Son.

59:35.600 --> 59:37.568
Do you see this?

59:37.680 --> 59:41.048
This is an anger prisoner.
A textbook example.

59:41.120 --> 59:42.724
See the fear, people?

59:42.800 --> 59:45.565
This boy is scared of the truth.

59:45.680 --> 59:49.002
Son, it breaks my heart to say this,

59:49.080 --> 59:53.210
but I believe you are a very troubled
and confused young man.

59:53.280 --> 59:56.489
You were searching for the answers
in the wrong places.

59:56.560 --> 01:00:01.521
You're right, actually. I am pretty
troubled and pretty confused.

01:00:01.600 --> 01:00:04.763
And I'm afraid. Really afraid. Really afraid.

01:00:04.840 --> 01:00:08.128
But I think you're the fucking Antichrist.

01:00:08.200 --> 01:00:10.328
[Shocked gasps]

01:00:10.400 --> 01:00:13.961
Get him out of here!
Who do you think you are?

01:00:14.040 --> 01:00:16.646
[Whistling and cheering]

01:00:21.160 --> 01:00:23.049
It's amazing.

01:00:23.160 --> 01:00:27.484
The man thinks he's telling the truth.
Everything he says is a fucking lie.

01:00:27.600 --> 01:00:29.841
Everything he says.

01:00:29.920 --> 01:00:33.049
Everyone thinks he's so rad.
He's such a chud.

01:00:33.120 --> 01:00:35.646
- Everything...
- Are you OK?

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:42.523
- Yeah...
- Sit down. Calm down.

01:00:48.160 --> 01:00:50.288
You ever hear of Grandma Death?

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:52.525
Who?

01:00:57.480 --> 01:01:00.165
<i>The Philosophy Of Time Travel.</i>

01:01:00.240 --> 01:01:02.163
What is this?

01:01:02.280 --> 01:01:04.362
She wrote it.

01:01:13.360 --> 01:01:15.169
I'm...

01:01:15.280 --> 01:01:16.964
I've been seeing stuff.

01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:19.884
Like a lot of really messed-up stuff.

01:01:21.200 --> 01:01:25.842
Chapters in there describe what
I've seen. It can't be a coincidence.

01:01:28.680 --> 01:01:32.924
[Monnitoft] Each vessel travels
along a vector through space time,

01:01:33.080 --> 01:01:34.969
along its centre of gravity.

01:01:35.040 --> 01:01:36.565
Like a spear?

01:01:38.520 --> 01:01:42.002
- Pardon?
- A spear coming out of your chest.

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:45.731
Um... sure, yeah.

01:01:45.840 --> 01:01:48.366
For the vessel to travel through time,

01:01:48.440 --> 01:01:51.683
it's got to find a portal, in this case a wormhole...

01:01:51.760 --> 01:01:57.324
Could these portals just appear
anywhere, any time?

01:01:57.440 --> 01:01:59.807
I think that's highly unlikely.

01:01:59.920 --> 01:02:03.481
What you're talking about is an act of God.

01:02:03.560 --> 01:02:06.006
If God controls time, time's pre-decided.

01:02:08.120 --> 01:02:12.284
- I don't follow.
- Every living thing has a set path.

01:02:12.360 --> 01:02:15.364
And if you could see your path or channel,

01:02:15.440 --> 01:02:20.890
you could see into the future.
Like... a form of time travel.

01:02:20.960 --> 01:02:23.770
You're contradicting yourself, Donnie.

01:02:23.840 --> 01:02:28.209
If we were able to see our destinies
manifest themselves visually,

01:02:28.280 --> 01:02:32.365
then we would be given a choice
to betray our chosen destinies.

01:02:32.440 --> 01:02:34.647
The fact that this choice exists

01:02:34.720 --> 01:02:38.645
would make all pre-formed destiny come to an end.

01:02:38.760 --> 01:02:40.888
Not if you travel in God's channel.

01:02:43.840 --> 01:02:49.961
Um... I'm not going to be able
to continue this conversation.

01:02:52.280 --> 01:02:55.602
- Why?
- I could lose my job.

01:02:56.440 --> 01:02:58.169
OK.

01:03:22.280 --> 01:03:24.362
[Birdsong]

01:03:49.520 --> 01:03:51.648
[laughs]

01:03:51.720 --> 01:03:54.371
Now you know where he lives.

01:03:56.640 --> 01:03:59.041
And they grow out of our chest...

01:03:59.120 --> 01:04:00.963
solar plexus?

01:04:01.040 --> 01:04:05.602
Like she described in the book.
The way they moved and smelled...

01:04:05.680 --> 01:04:07.728
Like they're workers.

01:04:08.840 --> 01:04:11.002
Assigned to each one of us.

01:04:11.080 --> 01:04:13.560
They just... They're like liquid.

01:04:15.120 --> 01:04:19.444
I followed it... into my parents' bedroom.

01:04:20.520 --> 01:04:22.727
What did you find?

01:04:27.160 --> 01:04:29.242
Nothing.

01:04:32.120 --> 01:04:35.681
So we call them IMGs.

01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:37.808
Infant Memory Generators.

01:04:37.880 --> 01:04:43.046
So you buy the glasses for an infant
and they wear them when they sleep.

01:04:44.160 --> 01:04:47.607
But inside the glasses are these slide photographs,

01:04:47.720 --> 01:04:50.803
and each one is of something peaceful or beautiful,

01:04:50.880 --> 01:04:53.406
whatever the parents want to put inside.

01:04:53.520 --> 01:04:56.410
What effect would this have on an infant?

01:04:57.280 --> 01:05:00.329
Well, nobody remembers their infancy.

01:05:00.400 --> 01:05:02.767
Anyone who says they do is lying.

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:05.486
We think this'll develop memory earlier in life.

01:05:05.600 --> 01:05:06.647
Yeah.

01:05:06.720 --> 01:05:12.602
Did you consider that darkness is part
of infants' natural development?

01:05:16.920 --> 01:05:18.251
No.

01:05:20.760 --> 01:05:22.569
Yeah.

01:05:22.640 --> 01:05:25.086
What if the parents put in pictures of Satan?

01:05:25.160 --> 01:05:27.288
Dead people, crap like that.

01:05:27.400 --> 01:05:29.880
Is that what you'd show your kids?

01:05:31.640 --> 01:05:36.726
Uh, well, I mean... didn't your dad stab your mom?

01:05:40.280 --> 01:05:43.284
Ha ha ha ha!

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:47.889
Get out.

01:05:49.520 --> 01:05:51.010
Gretchen!

01:05:51.120 --> 01:05:53.009
Gretchen. Gretchen.

01:05:53.080 --> 01:05:55.162
I'm sorry about those guys.

01:06:22.440 --> 01:06:26.286
- Two for Evil Dead, please.
- Two dollars.

01:06:34.640 --> 01:06:38.122
<i>[Slow, heavy banging]</i>

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:17.402
Why do you wear that stupid bunny suit?

01:07:22.400 --> 01:07:25.529
Why are you wearing that stupid man's suit?

01:07:34.880 --> 01:07:37.770
Take it off.

01:07:56.800 --> 01:07:59.849
What happened to your eye?

01:08:05.440 --> 01:08:07.761
I'm so sorry.

01:08:15.040 --> 01:08:17.122
Why do they call you Frank?

01:08:18.479 --> 01:08:20.926
It's the name of my father...

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:25.810
and his father before me.

01:08:29.560 --> 01:08:31.642
Frank?

01:08:35.160 --> 01:08:37.242
When's this gonna stop?

01:08:37.800 --> 01:08:39.928
You should already know that.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:42.082
[Laughs nervously]

01:08:43.399 --> 01:08:45.767
Watch the movie screen.

01:08:47.800 --> 01:08:50.246
There's something I want to show you.

01:08:58.680 --> 01:09:01.160
Have you ever seen a portal?

01:09:04.840 --> 01:09:07.366
[Clock chimes]

01:09:19.680 --> 01:09:22.206
Burn it to the ground.

01:10:13.800 --> 01:10:16.201
<i>♪ Woman singing wordless aria</i>

01:10:36.280 --> 01:10:40.126
OK. Now, girls, I want you to concentrate.

01:10:40.200 --> 01:10:42.601
Failure is not an option.

01:10:42.720 --> 01:10:46.202
Bethany, if you feel the need to vomit up there,

01:10:46.280 --> 01:10:49.284
- just swallow it.
- OK.

01:10:49.920 --> 01:10:52.446
Hey, you guys. Be lucky out there.

01:11:06.320 --> 01:11:07.924
[Whistle]

01:11:09.160 --> 01:11:11.208
Get off the stage, Cherita!

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:15.162
[Cheering and whistling]

01:11:15.280 --> 01:11:17.442
[boy] You suck!

01:11:24.840 --> 01:11:27.002
Hold on.

01:11:31.440 --> 01:11:33.602
That was really something.

01:11:33.680 --> 01:11:36.331
Thank you, Cherita Chen, with Autumn Angel.

01:11:37.480 --> 01:11:40.131
Now the moment we've all been waiting for.

01:11:40.200 --> 01:11:43.249
It is my distinct pleasure to introduce to you

01:11:43.360 --> 01:11:45.886
Emily Bates, Suzy Bailey,

01:11:45.960 --> 01:11:49.487
Samantha Darko, Beth Farmer and Joanie James.

01:11:49.560 --> 01:11:52.245
They are... Sparkle Motion.

01:11:52.320 --> 01:11:54.368
<i>♪ DURAN DURAN: Notorious</i>

01:11:54.480 --> 01:11:56.767
<i>♪ Notorious, notorious</i>

01:12:00.680 --> 01:12:03.729
<i>♪ No, no, notorious</i>

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:17.641
<i>♪ I can't read about it</i>

01:12:18.280 --> 01:12:21.602
<i>♪ Burns the skin from your</i> eyes

01:12:22.880 --> 01:12:26.646
<i>♪ I'll do fine without it</i>

01:12:27.560 --> 01:12:30.564
<i>♪ Here's one you don't compromise</i>

01:12:32.080 --> 01:12:36.085
<i>♪ Lies come hardly disguised</i>

01:12:36.840 --> 01:12:41.084
<i>♪ Betting me to fight it out, not wild about it</i>

01:12:41.560 --> 01:12:44.689
<i>♪ Spare your seedy judgments</i>

01:12:45.640 --> 01:12:48.530
<i>♪ Who says they're part of our lives?</i>

01:12:50.240 --> 01:12:51.890
<i>♪ You own the money</i>

01:12:51.960 --> 01:12:54.201
<i>♪ You control the witness</i>

01:12:54.760 --> 01:12:56.285
<i>♪ I'll leave you lonely</i>

01:12:56.400 --> 01:12:58.687
<i>♪ Don't monkey with my business</i>

01:12:58.760 --> 01:13:00.922
<i>♪ You've paid the profits</i>

01:13:01.000 --> 01:13:03.241
<i>♪ To justify your reasons</i>

01:13:03.800 --> 01:13:06.849
<i>♪ I heard you promise but I don't believe it</i>

01:13:06.920 --> 01:13:09.048
<i>♪ That's why I done it again...</i>

01:13:27.240 --> 01:13:29.322
[cheering]

01:13:35.680 --> 01:13:38.809
[girl] All right! Sparkle Motion!

01:13:41.960 --> 01:13:44.088
[Camera shutter clicks]

01:14:02.920 --> 01:14:05.048
[cheering]

01:14:36.880 --> 01:14:38.962
<i>[scream]</i>

01:14:41.800 --> 01:14:44.644
<i>[jaunty music]</i>

01:14:46.200 --> 01:14:48.646
How long was I asleep for?

01:14:49.560 --> 01:14:51.642
Whole movie.

01:14:59.520 --> 01:15:01.602
<i>[Police radio]</i>

01:15:01.680 --> 01:15:04.763
Captain, looks like we got another room back here.

01:15:06.280 --> 01:15:10.251
<i>[TV announcer] The blaze was
extinguished sometime after 8 p.m.</i>

01:15:10.320 --> 01:15:15.406
<i>Firefighters discovered what has
been called a "kiddie porn dungeon."</i>

01:15:15.480 --> 01:15:19.849
<i>Cunningham, who has become
a celebrity for his books and tapes,</i>

01:15:19.920 --> 01:15:21.604
<i>was arrested this morning...</i>

01:15:21.680 --> 01:15:23.728
Oh, my God!

01:15:25.080 --> 01:15:29.130
<i>Arson has not been ruled out
as the cause of the fire.</i>

01:15:29.200 --> 01:15:33.000
<i>A group of Cunning Vision employees...</i>

01:15:33.080 --> 01:15:35.606
Dad played golf with that guy.

01:15:35.680 --> 01:15:39.924
<i>...denied alleged links to a child
pornography publishing circuit.</i>

01:15:40.000 --> 01:15:44.085
<i>In a vicious statement, Cunningham
attacked fire department officials,</i>

01:15:44.160 --> 01:15:45.764
<i>claiming a vast conspiracy.</i>

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:51.688
[Dr. Cole] Karen, we don't think the
methods you've used are appropriate.

01:15:51.760 --> 01:15:56.527
What exactly about my methods
do you find inappropriate?

01:15:58.520 --> 01:16:01.000
I don't have time for a debate.

01:16:01.080 --> 01:16:03.924
I believe I've made myself clear.

01:16:04.000 --> 01:16:06.321
You call this clarity?

01:16:07.160 --> 01:16:10.960
You don't have a clue what it's like
to communicate with kids.

01:16:11.800 --> 01:16:14.963
And we are losing them to apathy.

01:16:17.160 --> 01:16:20.403
To this prescribed nonsense.

01:16:21.080 --> 01:16:23.128
They're slipping away.

01:16:23.240 --> 01:16:26.289
I am sorry that you have failed.

01:16:27.760 --> 01:16:30.491
If you'll excuse me, I have another appointment.

01:16:32.440 --> 01:16:34.727
You can finish out the week.

01:16:40.960 --> 01:16:44.009
[Screams]

01:17:03.680 --> 01:17:05.762
Good afternoon.

01:17:05.840 --> 01:17:10.289
It gives me great pleasure to
announce that the school dance team

01:17:10.400 --> 01:17:14.769
has been invited to perform
on Ed McMahon's Star Search '88

01:17:14.840 --> 01:17:17.571
in Los Angeles, California.

01:17:51.840 --> 01:17:53.922
No, it was ridiculous...

01:17:54.000 --> 01:17:56.048
I'll call you back.

01:17:57.160 --> 01:17:59.925
- Rose.
- Kitty.

01:18:00.720 --> 01:18:05.567
I'm sure you're aware of the horrible
allegations against Jim Cunningham.

01:18:05.640 --> 01:18:09.087
I saw it on TV.
Something about a kiddie porn...

01:18:09.240 --> 01:18:12.562
Oh, please! Don't use those words!

01:18:13.320 --> 01:18:17.405
It's obviously a conspiracy
to destroy an innocent man.

01:18:17.480 --> 01:18:22.441
I am going to spearhead the
Jim Cunningham defence campaign.

01:18:24.240 --> 01:18:28.564
Rose, I have to appear
at his arraignment tomorrow morning.

01:18:28.760 --> 01:18:32.810
The girls are scheduled to leave
for Los Angeles in the morning.

01:18:32.880 --> 01:18:37.204
As their coach, I was the
obvious choice to chaperone them...

01:18:37.280 --> 01:18:40.170
But now you can't go.

01:18:40.240 --> 01:18:41.890
- Yes.
- Hm.

01:18:41.960 --> 01:18:44.691
Now, believe me, of all the other mothers,

01:18:44.760 --> 01:18:46.842
I wouldn't dream of asking you.

01:18:46.920 --> 01:18:50.163
But none of the other mothers are available to go.

01:18:52.400 --> 01:18:54.482
I don't know, Kitty.

01:18:54.560 --> 01:18:57.530
It's a bad weekend. Eddie's in New York.

01:18:57.600 --> 01:19:01.924
Rose, I don't know if you realise

01:19:02.040 --> 01:19:05.681
what an opportunity this is for our daughters.

01:19:05.800 --> 01:19:10.806
This has been a dream of Samantha's
and all of ours for a long time.

01:19:11.480 --> 01:19:14.324
I made her lead dancer.

01:19:15.160 --> 01:19:20.007
Sometimes I doubt your commitment
to Sparkle Motion.

01:19:50.160 --> 01:19:52.811
Elizabeth will be in charge.

01:19:52.880 --> 01:19:55.451
She'll drive you to therapy.

01:19:56.240 --> 01:20:00.609
And if you need anything, promise me
you will call Dr. Thurman.

01:20:00.680 --> 01:20:02.762
OK.

01:20:11.200 --> 01:20:15.091
How does it feel to have a wacko for a son?

01:20:19.880 --> 01:20:22.008
It feels wonderful.

01:21:02.840 --> 01:21:06.287
What do I tell the others when they ask about you?

01:21:08.400 --> 01:21:11.131
Tell them everything is gonna be just fine.

01:21:13.240 --> 01:21:15.686
What's "cellar door"?

01:21:15.760 --> 01:21:19.128
[Sighs] This famous linguist once said

01:21:19.200 --> 01:21:22.921
that of all the phrases in the English language,

01:21:23.040 --> 01:21:27.364
of all the endless combinations
of words in all of history,

01:21:27.440 --> 01:21:31.047
that "cellar door" is the most beautiful.

01:21:33.400 --> 01:21:35.926
"Cellar door"?

01:22:06.760 --> 01:22:11.322
I promise that one clay
everything's gonna be better for you.

01:22:13.600 --> 01:22:15.682
Shut up!

01:22:28.480 --> 01:22:32.769
- I want to talk about your past today.
- No.

01:22:32.840 --> 01:22:37.368
I want to talk about you and your parents.

01:22:37.440 --> 01:22:41.240
They didn't buy me what I wanted for Christmas.

01:22:42.120 --> 01:22:44.885
What did you want for Christmas
that year?

01:22:45.520 --> 01:22:47.329
Hungry Hungry Hippos.

01:22:50.520 --> 01:22:54.923
How did you feel, being denied
these Hungry Hungry Hippos?

01:22:55.560 --> 01:22:57.005
Regret.

01:22:57.760 --> 01:23:00.411
What else makes you feel regret?

01:23:02.120 --> 01:23:04.202
